The source code of the compiler is organized in three main directories:

    src/Granite/Common

        This directory contains modules used throughout the compiler: names,
        source positions, etc.

    src/Granite/Behavioral

        This directory contains modules pertaining the behavioral aspect of
        the programming language: System FÏ‰ with row polymorphism.

    src/Granite/Organizational

        This directory contains modules pertaining the organizational aspect of
        the programming language: source files, top-level definitions, and
        interfaces.
